Comment.Text: if-then-else clause can be achieved using COND ? output-true : output-false
Some simple DSPs using only one input signal to perform mathematical operations
The Time signal is a sample box that generates a constant increasing signal
You can browse each box' documentation by selecting the box and pressing F1
You can use the letter 'X' (or 'x') for the first input. You can use up to 16 inputs. If you are using more than 1 input You have to use the letters a to n for inputs 1 to 16 respectively.
The Simple DSP box performs simple computations on input matrix These computations can be logical or arithmetical.
